      "prompt": "Franklin D. Roosevelt's New Deal (1933-1939) remains one of the most debated policy programs in American history. Supporters argue that it saved American democracy and capitalism by providing relief to millions and reforming the financial system. Critics from the left argue it did not go far enough to restructure the economy, while critics from the right contend it represented an unconstitutional expansion of federal power. Use the following excerpt and your knowledge of the period to answer the questions below.\n\nExcerpt: \"The New Deal was neither a revolution nor a restoration. It was a pragmatic improvisation that preserved the capitalist order while extending the reach of the federal government into economic and social life in ways that permanently altered the relationship between citizens and the state.\" - Adapted from a modern historical interpretation",
